which don't deliver.

76
00:03:32,098 --> 00:03:34,079
I don't believe most of those 30% of games

77
00:03:34,099 --> 00:03:36,680
that don't deliver started out as crooks.

78
00:03:36,740 --> 00:03:38,101
I think people have good intentions

79
00:03:38,181 --> 00:03:40,101
and sometimes fall prey to gravity.

80
00:03:40,562 --> 00:03:42,662
And that's the last thing you want to happen to you, right?

81
00:03:43,082 --> 00:03:44,823
Running out of funds is much, much worse

82
00:03:44,843 --> 00:03:46,424
than not getting funded in the first place.

83
00:03:47,364 --> 00:03:52,546
And above all, gravity is people not being paid,

84
00:03:52,966 --> 00:03:54,887
not being able to make payroll at the end of the month,

85
00:03:54,927 --> 00:03:56,287
whether it's you, whether it's your team.

86
00:03:59,068 --> 00:04:01,509
If you take nothing else away from today,

87
00:04:04,182 --> 00:04:06,543
Before you write another line of code,

88
00:04:06,603 --> 00:04:08,103
before you write another line of dialogue,

89
00:04:08,123 --> 00:04:09,344
before you draw another picture,

90
00:04:10,424 --> 00:04:13,505
